annotation.TEXT: First, let's enter door number 2 again...
Yeah...

And there's door number What! (Also, I grab the mushroom here to be fair, since I actually got hit twice while trying to "L" back there the first time). Now, if I enter Who on this screen, it'll go to the same place as What, which leads to...
Yellow shell = 3-6, Blue shell = 5-2.
Demo count: 5?
Okay, so I guess all that's left for me to do is go through door number 2 here... (after grabbing the mushroom and leaving behind a Tetris block...)
And that's exit number Cursed Memories!
And then enter door number The Phantom Menace. (I still don't know if this P-switch has any greater purpose than a single coin and some fish.)
Ah, I was wondering if the desync would cause Marina to jump out of there and kill herself. (Too bad there's no floor under the water here...)
Aaand... It appears that I've come out of door number 1 at the start. (Hmm... Maybe I got the HRtP and SoEW door labels switched from what they actually were meant to be.)
Alright, that's all 48 coins that were there. And I managed to not screw up while collecting them.
Oh, looks like she wants one more go at this!
Ooh, star coin. That's three already.
Huh. A P-switch... I guess I'll stomp it now, since I can't take it through door number The Phantom Menace...
Another door, a couple of Eeries (owww...), 18 fragile blocks, and a hidden mushroom. Hmm...
...Oh, no. Don't tell me... ZSNES has desynched on me again, hasn't it?
Alright, that's the last OWIE!!! Darn it all! ...Okay, what I was going to say was: "That's the last star coin, so I must've explored just about everywhere."
Huh? Hmm... If I position myself at the edge right here and press down + A or B, it looks like I go into the floor a bit, but I'm not actually clipping through.
Huh. A Boo ceiling, and door number Who, which is involved with Layer 2 shenanigans... Hey, if I carefully "L", I might be able to enter it now.
I wonder where I'd've ended up if I didn't ascend there...
And, strangely, that unlocked a path to 4-5, of all things. Huh...
And, further to the left, we have a third door. This is starting to remind me of that door-filled level of Mario on the Ghost Isle. Well, let's go with door number C here...
There doesn't appear to be anything further to the right, so door number beta it is.

Whoops. Well, I missed that pop up mushroom. However, if you fail to collect a pop up mushroom and it despawns off screen, you can make it respawn again by scrolling away from its original location and then coming back, just like this. (Good thing I can run against the sideways currents!)
The blue shell's victory there means that I'm playing 5-2 next! Supposedly, this mansion has many rooms...
Okay, I just came out of door HRtP, which is another two-way door, and there's vines... and also spikes.
Uh, oh. A countdown? Get ready...
Hey there Big Boo. How's it going? (Too bad it's not a cute one, like in ASMT...)
Another two-way door (which I'll call door number Hydrogen), and more air currents, of the lighter variety this time. Also, more Boo Chains.
...And then just spin jump off of Mr. Big Boo here in order to reach door number A.
Whoa! I get blown into the level by a water/wind current here.
Grumble... Grumble... Well, this sucks. I guess we get to watch Marina behave oddly for a while now.
Yes, this silly song will do quite nicely.
Okay, I'll take 40 from the ground.
D'oh, missed three more coins. Oh, well. Let's just finish this level. (Hey, I never heard the "Hurry up!" warning today!)
Of course, I don't want to be crushed by the crate, so I've gotta do this right.
However, all we get are the expected results. And then the footage ends shortly after returning to the overworld this time. So, I'm just going to cut back to where the desync first occurred...
Close call there. I had no idea that torpedo was right below me!
...5-2? Let's take a look at those voting results and find out!
Demo count: 4?
That unlocked 5-4. No surprise there. So, I could head to 5-4...
I'm glad that Boo Chain left me alone while I was trying to retrieve my feather there.
And now to backtrack through door numero uno...
And blue wins! That was a close one, and could've definitely gone either way!
Alright, what if I just chase door number Who to the right?
There we go!
Boo Blocks, eh? Also, note that that door I just came out of was two-way. We'll call that door number alpha. Now, let's see if I can get to door number beta over the spikes here...
Bonus game average so far: 101 / 14 = 7.214 1♥Ps each.
Well, I can enter it over here. Is that any different?
Okay, and now let's go through door number B. (I'll be sure to check door number A later, which might lead to the secret exit.)
...Ahem, I said, "let's enter door number 2 again"...
Huh. I wonder why there's a floor down here. Maybe to keep the Boo Chains from leaving the area?
Goal tape average so far: 1404 / 37 = 37.946 stars each.
That was another two-way door (we'll call it door numero uno this time), and this room's got air currents and a Boo Chain.
Gah! That's not okay. Don't start playing stupidly, now...
There's a 1♥P there, and... bah. I missed three coins. Oh, well.
That unlocks 5-3. However, I have a hunch about something in that mansion. Let me go back and check it out...
And then, go back through door number alpha...
I think I'll pick door number 2 here.
Whoa. Yeah, I've gotta be real careful when it comes to these currents.
...boss time! Yes, it's a Big Boo Boss battle, in an interesting room.
No clue. So, let's see what's behind door number The Phantom Menace...
Okay, I can use another flower... if I can manage to not overshoot it...
Hmm... Looks like this water level's going to specialize in currents, and maybe Torpedo Teds.
Whoops. Oh, that's interesting. You can actually run against the blue sideways currents!

Ah, right there. It was brief, but when I grabbed that brown block, I suddenly shifted down and was overlapping the purple block below for a moment. (And oddly, I somehow grabbed the lowest purple block there even though it was still covered from above. I'm lucky I didn't fall through there!)
That looks doubtful. I guess I'll have to go back through door number Hydrogen...
BGM: Wario Land 2 - Underwater Tunnels
That's the last star coin.
BGM: Touhou 12 - Captain Murasa
Gotcha this time! Now let's "A" and enter door numero dos.
Umm... Maybe I should've scoped out the top route a little more there.
I'm going to assume that that's just a bottomless pit down there. Okay, now let's enter door number SoEW up here...
Demo count: 6?
Well, let's head on over to 5-3 down here next, since I don't want to limit this video to just one level.
Well, fireballs might be useful on the fish here... I don't exactly think they'll help with the torpedos or currents, though.
Hmm... It doesn't look like I can reach door number Helium over there, unless there's a secret passage somewhere...
So, there's a door, and up here, we have another door...
Goal tape average so far: 1364 / 36 = 37.889 stars each.
Bah. That's okay, since there's a replacement flower right there.
Okay, so there's a door up here, but what's to the right?
Lots of coins here. Oh, but I'd better be careful not to get sucked into the munchers below. That would suck.
Got the mushroom, not that Marina needs it at this point... Let me see if I can find some fitting music for this...
Okay, and now, once again, we bounce off of Mr. Big Boo here to reach door number A...
I don't need another flower at the moment.
Now, about those Tetris shapes below: Both the purple and the light brown blocks are of the pick-up-and-toss variety, which are needed to defeat the Big Boo Boss.
...And lose my reserve flower to that mushroom... D'oh.
Hmm... Looks like the game will want me to "A" in order to reach door numero dos here.

Now, I remember that, not too long ago, someone wanted me to use the Captain Murasa music for a tie-breaker round, and I couldn't at the time, since there was no SMW port of it then. Well, this time...
BGM: Donkey Kong Land - Voices of the Temple
Yes, this lets me access door number Helium.
Demo count: 0
The yellow blocks on the right are ordinary turn blocks, and I assume the green ones break if hit by a thrown block, and the cyan ones break if hit by a fireball.
BGM: Lunar: Silver Star Story Complete - Blue Dragons...
Also, bonus game at ludicrous speed.
Well, I'm not getting what's in those ? blocks. (There was probably a power up in one of them, and maybe multiple coins in the other.)
That's four star coins, and another Boo Chain injury... Good thing I was right at a replacement power up. (They're sure generous with power ups around here, almost as much as "FLOWERS LEAD"!)
Now, the first time I was here, I had a glitch occur that could've killed me if I wasn't careful. I'll try to replicate it here if I can...
...Well?
And now to "L" here (yes, I got hit like this last time, but it's a safer way to "L"), and then stand on the crate and run to the left!
So, place your votes for either 3-6, 4-5, or 5-4, in order to determine where I'll go next time! To be continued...

...a port of Captain Murasa has become available (along with ports of many other Touhou 12 songs)! Also, have a new tie-breaker room while I'm at it. So, this time, the yellow shell represents 3-6, and the blue shell is 5-2. First to get a 1-up wins!
Okay, so that caused a single coin to appear, and dropped some fish into the room. So... What's that single coin for? Is it just merely a coin, or is it hinting at a secret?
ZSNES desync count: 2
Okay, I'm back to where ZSNES initially misread my movements as I approached door number 2, causing me to be half a tile to the left of where I should've been at the time I pressed up...
Marina wants another shot at this, but I don't see her getting very far...
Argh. I forgot to switch to my cape there, because my fireballs screw up the odd spin jump sound effect I was trying for.
Can't seem to simply fall against these upward currents, so I'll have to circle around and approach from below.
...A Boo Chain that I smack into because I don't know what I'm doing.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! So, will I be heading to 3-6? Or...
Be careful of the wind currents here, especially because they're on layer 2 and shift from side to side, so the way you're blown can change unexpectedly on you if you're not paying attention.
That was... kind of risky. However, entering door number Who there just leads me back here.
And there's exit number Hour of Darkness! Let's see if I can get more than 30 here...
